# Figma → Shopify Polaris Translation

This project converts Figma designs (see `design/data.json`, `design/Frame *.svg`, `design/Frame *.png`) into React pages built with `@shopify/polaris`. Always prefer Polaris components over raw HTML/CSS.

## Component mapping (from this project's design)

| Figma pattern | Polaris component | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Segmented tab switcher (e.g. "Workflows \| Functions") | `ButtonGroup variant="segmented"` + `<Button pressed>` | Not `Tabs` — Tabs are for full-page nav |
| Filter row with tabs + search/filter/sort icons | `IndexFilters` + `useSetIndexFiltersMode` | Single composite — don't wire icons manually |
| Table of records with selection | `IndexTable` inside `LegacyCard` + `useIndexResourceState` | Wrap every row in `<IndexTable.Row>` |
| Status pill | `Badge` with `tone` prop | `attention` (orange), `success` (green), `warning`, `critical`, `info` |
| "Create new ▾" dropdown button | `<Button disclosure>` | Pair with `Popover` + `ActionList` for the menu |
| Pagination control | `Pagination` with `label` prop | Right-align via `<InlineStack align="end">` |
| Dark filled primary button | `<Button variant="primary">` | |
| Spacing/stacking | `BlockStack` (vertical) / `InlineStack` (horizontal) | Do **not** use deprecated `Stack` / `Inline` |

## Deprecated components — never use

Use the non-deprecated replacements:

```tsx
// BAD
import { Stack, Inline, Card, Tabs, Heading } from '@shopify/polaris';

// GOOD
import {
  BlockStack,      // replaces Stack (vertical)
  InlineStack,     // replaces Inline (horizontal)
  LegacyCard,      // when you need the old Card behavior
  Card,            // prefer the new Card for new surfaces
  Text,            // replaces Heading, DisplayText, Subheading, Caption, TextStyle
} from '@shopify/polaris';
```

## Color / token handling

- Never hardcode `rgba(...)` from Figma fills. Let Polaris components handle color via their `tone`/`variant` props.
- The Figma `VARIABLE_ALIAS` tokens in `data.json` cannot be resolved — `design/variables.json` returns enterprise-only. Fall back to semantic Polaris props.

## Required file pattern

A generated Polaris page should:

1. Be a default-exported functional component
2. Wrap content in `<Page>` (optional `title`, `primaryAction`, `backAction`)
3. Use `BlockStack gap="400"` for vertical sections
4. Keep data arrays (`ITEMS`, etc.) as module-level constants until wired to an API

